de.thkoeln.bibl.api.lms.slnp.message

Class ResponseMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.thkoeln.bibl.api.lms.slnp.message.Message
      • de.thkoeln.bibl.api.lms.slnp.message.ResponseMessage
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConnectResponseMessage

    public class ResponseMessage
extends Message
    Implements a SLNP response message. The class describes the basic format of a response message. A response message has the following format: CODE [Key:]Value

        public ResponseMessage(java.lang.String msg,
                       java.lang.String pattern)
                throws java.util.regex.PatternSyntaxException,
                       MessageFormatException
        Initialize a ResponseMessage with a raw SLNP message and a pattern, which defines the message format with matching groups.
        Parameters:
        msg - the raw SLNP server message
        pattern - the format as REGEX string
        Throws:
        java.util.regex.PatternSyntaxException - if the pattern's syntax is invalid
        MessageFormatException - if the message has a invalid format
